# Deployment

Oxidoc generates a fully static site in the `dist/` directory. Run the build command:

<CodeBlock language="bash">
oxidoc build
</CodeBlock>

This produces a `dist/` folder with all HTML, CSS, JS, and Wasm files ready to serve. Deploy it to any static hosting provider.

<CardGrid>
<Card title="GitHub Pages" icon="🐙" href="/deployment/github-pages">
Free hosting for public repos with GitHub Actions CI/CD.
</Card>
<Card title="Vercel" icon="▲" href="/deployment/vercel">
Instant deployments with preview URLs for every pull request.
</Card>
<Card title="Netlify" icon="🌐" href="/deployment/netlify">
Continuous deployment with branch previews and form handling.
</Card>
</CardGrid>
